description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to an Assessment Day on Friday 20th November 2020. Please note this will be either a morning or afternoon session to be confirmed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit motivated, enthusiastic and clinically capable nurse to join our team for our 19 bedded Ward at Newquay Community Hospital. The Nurse role requires the post holder to be committed to the ongoing development of the ward and multi-disciplinary team working. We aim to deliver the highest standard of patient and rehabilitative care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require motivated, forward thinkers with a “can-do” attitude and a passion for nursing. In return we will support you in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal applicant will possess a good level of organizational, communication, discharge planning experience and clinical skills relevant to the post and be able to act as a positive role model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be undertaking both day shifts from 07:30 – 20:00 or Night duties 19:30 –08:00 on a rotational basis in order to support 24 hour nursing care, 7 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGemma TaylorJob titleSisterEmail addressgemma.taylor43@nhs.netTelephone number01637834809&lt;/p&gt;
